programme.title: Call the Midwife
programme.desc: The nuns and midwives move into their new premises following the explosion that wrecked the old Nonnatus House, and are joined by fresh arrival Sister Winifred - a kindly-but-naive young woman. Jenny becomes concerned about new mother Merle's mental state and the welfare of her baby, who isn't feeding properly. Dr Turner believes it could be something more serious - although the mystery is eventually solved by the last person anyone would have expected. Chummy is struggling to adjust to her new role as a housewife and mother, and organises an open day at the community centre. Jessica Raine, Stephen McGann and Miranda Hart star

programme.title: Call the Midwife
programme.desc: Trixie's feathers are ruffled when Jenny is promoted, but the new Acting Sister has more to worry about after a mother-to-be reveals the baby she is carrying was not fathered by her husband - and to complicate matters, the real father is black. Cynthia is inspired by a lecture on natural childbirth, convinced it will help an overly anxious patient, while Alec and his friends try to persuade Jenny to join them on a CND march. Jessica Raine, Helen George and Bryony Hannah star in the 1950s-set nursing drama

programme.title: Call the Midwife
programme.desc: Sister Julienne receives an SOS from Holloway Prison, whose usual maternity workers have been struck down by illness, and when she and Trixie step in to help, the nun puts her reputation on the line to prevent a heavily pregnant convict having her unborn baby taken away by social services. Shelagh faces heartache when a routine pregnancy check reveals something far more serious, Alec has a confession for Jenny, and Fred takes the gang to the theatre to celebrate Chummy's birthday - only for the trip to end in disaster. Lacey Turner, best known as EastEnders' Stacey Branning, guest stars

programme.title: Call the Midwife
programme.desc: Jenny has an eventful few days, starting with a patient who as well as having herself to worry about, is also struggling to cope with her mother, an agoraphobic who hasn't been outside for at least 12 years. On top of that, Alec asks the midwife to accompany him to Brighton for the weekend, leaving her wondering if his intentions are strictly honourable. However, things soon take a tragic turn. Meanwhile, Shelagh joins the local choir to take her mind off her problems. Jessica Raine, Leo Staar and Laura Main star

programme.title: Call the Midwife
programme.desc: The nuns and midwives are busy preparing for Sister Evangelina's surprise jubilee celebrations, marking 50 years since she took her vows, but a face from the past threatens to ruin the party for the guest of honour. It's back to business when a young woman with Down's syndrome is brought in feeling unwell. To everyone's surprise, they discover she is six months pregnant, causing some of them to think the worst, and the staff are joined by new nurse Patsy, whose sense of humour and no-nonsense attitude make her an instant hit

programme.title: Call the Midwife
programme.desc: Trixie is chuffed when local curate Tom invites her to join him for a day of cricket, sending her to work with a spring in her step. Is love on the cards for the young midwife? Shelagh's infertility has made her think long and hard about what she wants in life, so she approaches her husband with an idea, while Patsy upsets a young mother in the clinic and is moved to the district rota, where she works tirelessly to diagnose a docker's unusual symptoms

programme.title: Call the Midwife
programme.desc: Cynthia is concerned during a visit as she feels new mum Pamela is overly anxious, so Dr Turner arranges for a psychiatrist to come in. However, they soon discover both mother and baby have gone missing. Meanwhile, Jenny, on secondment, begins to see cracks in the establishment, Chummy discovers her mother has walked out on her father, and Trixie struggles to hide her disappointment when Tom cancels a date. Guest starring Sophie Rundle

programme.title: Call the Midwife

programme.desc: Jake Peralta is a talented but carefree detective at Brooklyn's 99th Precinct. He and his eclectic group of colleagues are used to having a commanding officer who doesn't make them work too hard or follow the rules too closely. But when tightly-wound Captain Ray Holt, a man with a lot to prove, takes over, he is determined to make his dysfunctional team of detectives into the best precinct squad in Brooklyn

programme.title: Brooklyn Nine-Nine
programme.desc: When Jake turns up late for morning roll call, Captain Holt responds by assigning him to a minor graffiti case and then closely monitoring his every move. But the investigation soon turns into a major headache when the vandal turns out to be the Deputy Police Commissioner's son. Gina's psychic friend Carlene pays a visit to the precinct to help the detectives with a drugs case, but she manages to upset Charles by making a prediction about his romantic life

programme.title: The Big Bang Theory
programme.desc: Sheldon has been awarded a prestigious prize by the university but is scared of collecting the gong at an awards ceremony because he knows he'll have to give a speech. Penny tries to gee him up with rousing references to X-Men

programme.title: The Big Bang Theory
programme.desc: Leonard tells Penny that he loves her but doesn't get the response he would have liked. The gang go bowling and get a surprise when Sheldon's enemy, Star Trek actor Wil Wheaton, is playing in the opposing team. Will Sheldon get revenge on Wil?

programme.title: Baby Daddy
programme.desc: Ben helps Tucker with the charade of posing as a lawyer because Tucker hasn't told his father that he dropped out of law school and now works in TV. Riley gets a crush on a British guy, but Bonnie mistakenly thinks she's fallen for Danny. The family visit a Renaissance Fair

programme.title: Baby Daddy
programme.desc: Ben is not thrilled when Riley asks him to hang out with her new British boyfriend Philip. But things go horribly wrong when Ben's attempts to flirt with a student put Philip's job at the college - and his visa - in jeopardy. Tucker fakes a British accent while trying to attract dates

programme.title: Brooklyn Nine-Nine
programme.desc: When Captain Holt receives death threats, Peralta is put in charge of his security: a responsibility he enjoys and abuses as much as he can. Santiago attempts to get the precinct to take a Christmas photo for Holt, but runs up against a lack of enthusiasm and Diaz's refusal to smile. Jeffords tries to pass his psych evaluation, but it takes an emergency to get him back to his old self

programme.title: Brooklyn Nine-Nine
programme.desc: In order to catch the Pontiac Bandit, a car thief he has been tracking for years, Peralta attempts to make a deal with a suspect Diaz has just arrested. The station tries to accommodate a scooter-bound Boyle's every need when he returns to work after being shot in the line of duty, and Captain Holt struggles to find a home for two puppies

programme.title: The Big Bang Theory
programme.desc: Sheldon is scared that he is in a relationship when Amy asks him to meet her mother, and Leonard asks Howard and Bernadette to set him up because he is the only person in the group without a girlfriend

programme.title: The Big Bang Theory
programme.desc: Leonard tries to keep everyone from finding out that he spent the night with Raj's sister, but Sheldon finds out and concocts an elaborate story to help him keep the secret from Raj

programme.title: Hollyoaks
programme.desc: Scott convinces Diane that he didn't do anything, while Darren tries to comfort Mandy but she can't forgive him for ending their relationship

programme.title: The Big Bang Theory
programme.desc: Sheldon has to go back to Texas when his sister goes into labour, and while he is away the gang gather at the flat to decorate the Christmas tree. They ponder on how things would have turned out if they had never met Sheldon, and realise how much he has changed their lives

programme.title: The Big Bang Theory
programme.desc: After Leonard tries to help Penny following a failed role on a TV show, she makes an important decision

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off: An... (?)
Father Ted
programme.desc: Ted gets the chance to appear on prestigious TV show Faith of Our Fathers. Could this be the opportunity for him to find television stardom and escape from Craggy Island? No. His best efforts, and some of his worst, are frustrated by Father Dougal, Father Jack and the arrival of Funland - the world's worst funfair

programme.title: Father Ted
programme.desc: For six years, Father Stone has been coming to Craggy Island, which is at least seven years too many for Ted, Dougal and Jack. Ted tries everything to get him to leave, but when Father Stone finds himself on the receiving end of a bolt of lightning, Ted becomes equally desperate to get him back

programme.title: 8 Out of 10 Cats Does Countdown
programme.desc: Jimmy Carr hosts the comedy panel game, as Sean Lock and Henning Wehn take on special guest captain Bill Bailey and Jessica Hynes. Tom Allen joins Susie Dent in Dictionary Corner, while Rachel Riley looks after the numbers and letters

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Winter Sun (?)
Four in a Bed
programme.desc: The final visit of the week is to The Old Lodge Hotel in Gosport, Hampshire, where publicans Mike Pearce and Tash Thorne like to mix business with pleasure. On arrival, castle proprietor Karen Hepker - who's on her own this visit - is allocated the honeymoon suite, but she's left disappointed with the level of luxury while Clive and Jenny Aylett find a dubious looking splash guard in the shower

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Winter Sun (?)
Food Unwrapped
programme.desc: Jimmy Doherty, Kate Quilton and Matt Tebbutt present some favourite investigations. Jimmy takes to the skies above Israel to join the battle to protect the bell pepper crop from the Mediterranean fruit fly, but is amazed to learn that it's not insecticide that he's helping to spread across the desert. Kate heads to the Amazon rainforest to investigate rumours that the Brazil nuts on UK supermarket shelves are all radioactive. And, with goat milk producers currently having no use for thousands of young male goats, Matt takes to the streets to find out how goat meat goes down with the public

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: Emma and David Martin-Jewell from south Wales are looking for a dream holiday home for them and their young family in Fort Lauderdale, Florida. Emma has been holidaying in the US since she was a child and has long dreamed of owning a holiday home there. Ben Hillman shows Emma and David five homes for their £275,000 budget

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: Leyla and Will Moore from Leeds both have hectic working lives, but now that the five kids they have between them are grown up, they're ready to slow down a little and buy their own place in the sun. For their budget of £350,000 Scarlette Douglas shows them five stunning villas on the Algarve in Portugal

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: The competition starts at The Oak pub and B&B in Charing, Kent, where new landlady Natalie Palmer hopes to be crowned best-value B&B of the week. While spiritually enlightened Katherine Armitage and Stewart Johnston are pleased they've got room for their yoga mats, both Dennis Gilligan and Gary Coaley and Mike and Denise Mitchell aren't blown away by their extractor fans. At breakfast, Natalie goes it alone in the kitchen, which leaves her guests admiring her work ethic, but the issue of the extractor fans comes back to haunt her

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: The second visit is to the village of Worstead in Norfolk, where Dennis Gilligan runs The White Lady, which he claims has a ghostly extra guest. Most of the guests are firing on all cylinders at a clay pigeon shoot, but peace loving Katherine is left feeling shell-shocked while some of the men in the competition are determined to be the top gun

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: The third visit of the week is to Cranleigh House B&B in Coombe Martin, Devon, where former couple Katherine Armitage and Stewart Johnston offer alternative accommodation for fans of yoga and spiritual enlightenment. On a local hill top, they hope that the group will send out energy for world peace and healing, but Mike and Denise question whether the whole thing is a joke, while Dennis and Gary struggle to keep a straight face

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: The fourth and final visit is to Paignton on the English Riviera where Mike and Denise Mitchell are the new kids on the block, having only opened the doors to their B&B, Beaches, a few weeks earlier. Over dinner there are revelations when Mike tells his guests about his other career... as a movie star

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: With all the visits over, the B&B owners come together to confront their rivals and discover what they've been paid

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: East London fashionista Simran Samra hosts a glitz and glam night for her guests: doctor Chintu Gademsetty, comedian Yoshki Greenberg, City boy Alan Price and businesswoman Delia Elliot. Simran cooks meat even though she's a vegetarian and buys wine although she knows nothing about it, and her main course isn't a success. And when Alan's overbearing nature rubs a few of the guests up the wrong way Simran attempts to create a diversion with some comedy accents

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: In east London, laid-back comedian Yoshki Greenberg aims to throw a relaxing dinner party and give her guests a good laugh. And she has a surprise up her sleeve: animal-themed pyjama suits for her guests. Unfortunately not all of them are comfortable wearing somebody else's clothes, especially when they haven't been washed. Can Yoshki cheer her guests up with her stand-up comedy act?

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: In east London, Jack-the-Lad Alan Price aims to wow his guests with a medieval-themed feast. After two nights of disappointing food, Alan hopes he can raise the standard with an ambitious menu. But his dinner party doesn't get off to the best start when his medieval table decoration - a whole pig's head - panics vegetarian Simran and earns Alan a tongue-lashing from Delia. And Alan's dirty plates and hapless hosting don't impress Chintu or Yoshki

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: The competition continues in east London. Cordon bleu cook Delia Elliot has played down her menu but her guests' expectations are still high. Delia's confident she can teach her young guests a thing or two about how to throw a good dinner party. But not all of them want to listen; especially prankster Alan, who has such a row with Delia that Simran hides under the table

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: In east London, doctor Chintu Gademsetty is confident of winning with his 1980s-themed dinner party. But he needs to create a cheery atmosphere following the tensions of the past two nights. The night gets off to a good start with Chintu's MC Hammer costume and Knight Rider car. And although Delia refuses to take part in his 80s dance competition, the host impresses with his breakdancing. But does Chintu have any chance of claiming the £1000 prize?

programme.title: Vet on the Hill
programme.desc: Dr Scott Miller helps beagle puppy Watson, who has come off second best in a play fight with a friend's cat. Scott's new vet Jo and veterinary nurse Gemma are taking a pregnant stray cat to foster carer Penny. Ali brings in her new rescue dog Mabel for a check-up on her troublesome knee. And Scott is asked to look at a fox that has been run over and appears to have a broken leg

programme.title: The Secret Life of the Zoo
programme.desc: Sumatran tiger mum Kirana faces losing her two sons, Topan and Jaya, who are fully grown and being moved to other zoos to start families of their own. Keepers are unsure how Kirana, and her remaining cub, daughter Kasarna, will react to the departure of the boys. Meanwhile, one of Chester Zoo's most secretive and sensitive animals, Oana the anoa, gives birth to a calf, Nani. But Oana's anxiety after the birth threatens Nani's health: she's licking her so much that the calf is losing its fur

programme.title: The Supervet
programme.desc: There's a dramatic emergency when a Staffordshire bull terrier called Lulu is hit by a car and her pelvis is smashed in more than 25 pieces. Professor Noel Fitzpatrick's only option is to pin the larger pieces back together in an operation that will require all his expertise. A giant schnauzer called Florence has lost her tail wag with a sore knee. And a pointy-eared Jack Russell called Muffin has a mysterious problem with her back legs

programme.title: Grand Designs
programme.desc: Kevin McCloud follows an epic Grand Design. Back in 2006, Stefan Lepkowski and Ania Shabowska set out to transform a derelict mill cottage in the beautiful Northumberland countryside into a cutting-edge contemporary home. But this was never going to be a simple build. Their ambitious plans turned out to be three projects rolled into one. First, the restoration of a Georgian cottage, then the reconstruction of an old watermill, and third a dramatic modern steel and glass atrium linking it all together. On top of all that, Stefan insisted on doing most of the work himself on a totally unrealistic budget. Over the years Stefan stubbornly refuses to accept help, the bank refuse him any more money, and the project turns into a gruelling battle of wills that almost grinds to a halt. Two children and five years later, through sheer determination, Stefan and Ania finally complete their Grand Design

programme.title: Cheaper By the Dozen 2
programme.desc: (2005, Comedy) Tom and Kate Baker and their 12 children are enjoying a summer holiday together at their lakeside cabin before the last of the kids flies the nest. Comedy sequel, with Steve Martin, Eugene Levy, Bonnie Hunt and Hilary Duff

programme.title: Romancing the Stone
programme.desc: (1984, Comedy) A romantic novelist goes in search of her kidnapped sister in the steamy jungles of South America, only to become the target of a villainous general who demands as a ransom the valuable treasure map in her possession. Help is at hand in the form of a craggy daredevil fortune hunter, who has his eye on a share of the profits. Comedy adventure, starring Michael Douglas, Kathleen Turner and Danny DeVito

programme.title: Titanic
programme.desc: (1997, Romance) A party of explorers studying the sunken remains of the famous liner meets an elderly woman who was a passenger on the ill-fated maiden voyage. She recounts how she boarded the ship while on the brink of being forced into marriage by her family, and was stopped from killing herself by a penniless artist. She fell in love with her saviour, but the disaster on the horizon meant their time together was doomed to be short. James Cameron's Oscar-winning romantic drama, starring Kate Winslet, Leonardo DiCaprio, Billy Zane, Kathy Bates and Bill Paxton

programme.title: Last Vegas
programme.desc: (2013, Comedy) A sixtysomething confirmed bachelor finally decides to settle down with his much younger girlfriend. He and three friends decide to mark the occasion by reliving their wild youth with a trip to Las Vegas - but they find that both the city and each other have changed since their glory days. Comedy, starring Michael Douglas, Robert De Niro, Morgan Freeman and Kevin Kline

programme.title: Red
programme.desc: (2010, Thriller) A retired CIA agent survives an assassination attempt and realises something in his past has made him a target. He sets out to reunite the members of his old hit squad to find out who is trying to kill them and why, but in the process, uncovers dangerous secrets. Action thriller, with Bruce Willis, Morgan Freeman, John Malkovich and Helen Mirren

programme.title: Dracula Untold
programme.desc: (2014, Fantasy) A Romanian knight fights to defend his homeland against Turkish invaders. Faced with overwhelming odds, he enters into a dangerous bargain to gain supernatural powers so he can drive off his enemies - but the deal could cost him his humanity as he transforms into a terrifying monster. Fantasy adventure, starring Luke Evans, Dominic Cooper and Charles Dance

At first it's all a bit much to take in, as he learns the modern world is teeming with deities and their offspring. And things take a turn for the worse when Zeus (Sean Bean) suspects Percy of theft after the lightning bolt that confers supreme, terrifying power goes missing. With his mother kidnapped and the errant super weapon threatening to cause a catastrophic clash of the gods, Percy sets off to recover the artefact. Jerry Welbach (Pitt) is a low-level Mafia "mechanic" whose ineptitude is countered by frequent (but unpredictable) bursts of dumb luck. Jerry's girlfriend Samantha (Roberts) wants him to get out of the business, and after his latest blunder lands capo Arnold Margolese (Gene Hackman) in jail, so does mid-level crime kingpin Bernie Nayman (Bob Balaban). But Bernie insists that Jerry do one last errand for the mob before they let him find employment elsewhere -- he has to go to Mexico and recover a rare and very valuable pistol, which is said to be cursed. While Samantha objects to Jerry taking the assignment, he isn't in much of a position to argue; Jerry heads south of the border, while Samantha, in a huff, sets out for Las Vegas. programme.desc: Matt Reeves' smart monster thriller has been favourably compared to The Blair Witch Project , with which it shares the concept of using "found" camcorder footage to reveal its horrors. The film opens at a party for Manhattan yuppie Rob Hawkins where the revelries are interrupted by a loud explosion. As he and his friends Hud, Jason, Marlena and Lily emerge onto the street, the head of the Statue of Liberty cartwheels past them. Something very big, scaly and angry is trashing the city, and one of the targets is a high-rise where Beth, Rob's girlfriend lives. The group set out in a rescue bid, with Hud recording everything as they make their way through what has become a nightmarish New York, threatened both by the monster (only ever half-glimpsed, making it even more terrifying) and the parasitic lice it sheds, which develop a taste for human flesh. Will all, or indeed any, of the group make it to safety? The footage tells their stories in shocking, handheld detail in this superbly paced movie

programme.title: The Hurt Locker (2008)
programme.desc: Kathryn Bigelow's multiple-Oscar-winning film is a compelling fact-based, Iraq-set bomb disposal drama, scripted by journalist Mark Boal, drawing on his experiences while embedded with a United States Army Explosive Ordnance Disposal team in 2004. The focus is on the complex characters making up Bravo Company, who disable and destroy improvised explosive devices. The days are ticking down to the end of the bomb squad's tour, but their role puts the team in harm's way around the clock. And it doesn't help that one of the team is addicted to risk taking and pays scant attention to standard procedure, putting other lives in danger, as well as his own. The Hurt Locker provides a tense glimpse into the lives of these extraordinary men, and also probes the various psychologies of people whose job could kill them at any moment, as well as - briefly - exploring how they cope once away from their adrenaline-soaked vocation. Also starring Anthony Mackie, Ralph Fiennes, Guy Pearce, Brian Geraghty and Evangeline Lilly

He embarks on a desperate quest for revenge that sees him fighting in front of thousands of Romans in the Coliseum. Directed by acclaimed filmmaker Ridley Scott, Gladiator re-creates the glory of Ancient Rome with Academy Award-winning special effects. A modern classic. Starring Russell Crowe Joaquin Phoenix, Richard Harris, Connie Nielsen and Oliver Reed

programme.desc: Tim Burton's dark fantasy stars Johnny Depp in the title role, a humanoid construct made by The Inventor but whose hands - long, sharp blades - are left unfinished following his creator's death. Discovered alone in his Gothic castle by Avon lady Peg Boggs, he is taken home to her suburban family: husband Bill, daughter Kim and son Kevin. Edward soon becomes a social hit; thanks to his hands, he is in demand for exotic dog styling, hair dos and hedge clipping. But Kim's boyfriend plays a cruel trick on him which turns the neighbourhood against him. With Edward now an outcast, hunted by a baying mob of suburbanites, only Kim can help him return to his true home. Edited for language
